large part c</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">aused by immobility</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">cost</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> of dedicating massive areas of cities to road surfaces and parking. This would include for example damage caused by flooding due to poor water absorption in areas that are heavily sealed</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">costs of environmental damage</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">costs of clea</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ning up after cars</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">costs of having to sound proof buildings near roads</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">costs of pollution damage to public and private buildings</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">costs of licencing, policing, administration and accounting associated with motorised transport</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">This is a partial list, but a</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> t</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ally of such costs </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">will help:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">the committee to begin to appreciate that any costs absorbed through infrastructure investment in cycling are miniscule in comparison to the massive costs absorbed to maintain motorised transport.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">to counter the idiotic statem</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ents made by motorists who suggest that the road tax they pay covers the costs of damage</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">us to begin to understand that motorised vehicles cost society heavily in many different ways</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Finally, the committee should appreciate that</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> with the majority of voter</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">s being motorists, politicians will find it </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">difficult to do the right thing with regard to transport policy. </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">There will always be costs associated with the need for transport.   We should understand these costs and then appreciate that progress can be ma</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">de with cycling, which incurs far fewer costs and even provides health benefit.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">It is a no-</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">brainer, but there are a lot of</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> low-brainers out there </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">who</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> have been stopping progress away</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> from our bike unfriendly infrastructure.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>